article.headline: Lamar 66, Air Force 59 (OT)
article.story: BEAUMONT, Texas (AP) -- Teddy Davis' two free throws started an 8-0 overtime run for Lamar, which beat Air Force 66-59 on Monday night. Jason Grant hit two free throws with 42 seconds left in regulation, giving Lamar a 50-47 lead. Then Nick Welch of Air Force drove in for a layup and was fouled on the play. Welch, who scored a game-high 20 points, hit the free throw to complete the three-point play, tying the game at 50. Alan Daniels tried a 3-pointer for the Cardinals at the buzzer, but it was no good. The Cardinals outscored the Falcons 16-9 during overtime. Raymond Anthony led Lamar (4-2) with 15 points on 5-of-10 from the field, including four 3-pointers. Davis added 13, and Thomas Fairley had 12 points and nine rebounds. Antoine Hood scored 13 points for Air Force (6-4). Lamar outrebounded the Falcons 42-21, and the Cardinals' bench players outscored the Air Force bench 41-5. Lamar led 24-19 at halftime.
